	(93,'http://blogbaladi.com/run-gloria-run/','Run Gloria Run','http://blogbaladi.com/images/2010mds7.jpg','Gloria Nasr was born in Beirut but has been living in France since 1995. She is planning a 5000km run for Peace from Par...','blogbaladi',1361961960,'<p><img src=\"http://blogbaladi.com/images/2010mds7.jpg\" alt=\"2010mds7\" width=\"400\" height=\"308\"></p>\n<p>Gloria Nasr was born in Beirut but has been living in France since 1995. She is planning a 5000km run for Peace from Paris all the way to Beirut. She will start her run on the 7th of April 2013 at the Champs Elysees in Paris and arrive to Beirut in August.</p>\n<p>You can check out more about her run [<a href=\"http://www.parisbeyrouth-en-courant.com/0inter.html\">Here</a>] and help achieve her goal [<a href=\"https://www.bankeez.com/fr/payment/pot/53b0216dec34b74e6d098295426a2758#.US3hl_JUGSo\">Here</a>].</p>\n<p><img src=\"http://blogbaladi.com/images/gloria-425x313.png\" alt=\"gloria\" width=\"425\" height=\"313\"><br><em>I wonder if it will be safe to run across Syria when she gets there</em></p>\n<p><em>via <a href=\"http://www.haykhabriyeh.com/gloria-nasr-courir-pour-la-paix/\">HayKhabriyeh</a></em></p>'),
	(94,'http://ginosblog.com/2013/02/27/clvii-customized-and-unique-fashion-opens-in-first-branch-outside-of-paris-in-beirut/','CLVII: Customized and Unique Fashion Opens in First Branch Outside of Paris in Beirut','http://ginoraidy.files.wordpress.com/2013/02/wpid-20130226_124106.jpg?w=610','So, I was in Saifi Village over the weekend to check out the exhibition at Vick Vanlian’s gallery, which I must say wa...','ginosblog',1361961480,'<p><a href=\"http://ginoraidy.files.wordpress.com/2013/02/wpid-20130226_124106.jpg\"><img alt=\"wpid-20130226_124106.jpg\" src=\"http://ginoraidy.files.wordpress.com/2013/02/wpid-20130226_124106.jpg?w=610\"></a></p>\n<p>So, I was in Saifi Village over the weekend to check out the exhibition at Vick Vanlian’s gallery, which I must say was extremely interesting: morbid and sexually suggestive paintings of Popeye that certainly put them in a light I had never even dared consider. Check it out, you won’t be disappointed.</p>\n<p>Anyway, I stepped outside and noticed a shop a few meters away with studded kicks, caps and skull speakers which reminded me of the places in the Beverly Center in Los Angeles. Fashion in Los Angeles is often thought of as the Hollywood Red Carpet-style haute couture by massive names and even more massive price tags. But, the average Los Angelino will probably be sporting a 50USD Diamond Supply Co tee with a smart-ass quote on it and a diamond insignia. I liked these independent shops because their stuff was often limited quantity for each tee, cap, etc. Which means you’re probably gonna be the only one wearing it when you’re out.</p>\n<p>If I could count how many identical Louis Vuitton clutches I see every weekend at White, I wouldn’t because I’d be busy enjoying my time doing something fun. But, you get the idea. Paying lotsa money to carry something everyone else is carrying isn’t always what I’m into. I like wearing stuff that I know no one else is gonna be wearing and I sure love seeing a woman in something that makes me think “nice” and not because it’s revealing, but because it’s different from the H&M stuff that it seems every woman on Earth goes to buy at the same exact time.</p>\n<p>Getting back to the store, I went in looking for some Diamond Supply Co. caps but soon enough I found out it was actually a French store, that had just opened the other day and was still finalizing their showroom. The name was hard to get at first, CLVII (it’s 157 in Roman numerals) which signifies the address of the Paris street the store originated on.</p>\n<p>After a very pleasant tour of the place with Zaynab, I got to actually meet the designer, Julien, who I had a chat with about his concept which I actually was interested in (a rarity when it comes to Fashion).</p>\n<p>Julien explained that the idea behind his brand was that even though it’s noticed and often by important people like Rihanna, Lil’Wayne and Jason De Rulo, he tries to keep a lid on it and relies mostly on word of mouth of his customers, who are often members of Gulf countries’ Royal Families doing a layover in Paris on their way to the States and stock up on customized, somewhat over-the-top couture from CLVII.</p>\n<p>Julien felt traditional brands were getting dull and boring, and that every piece of upscale fashion was the same. That’s why, he’d take people’s 5000USD bags, rip it up, poke holes in it and add elements to it that would “pimp it up”. So, now, his customers can have an LV clutch that’s slightly more noticeable.</p>\n<p>Of course, most of us can’t afford to blow 5K on a bag, but do wear G-shocks, converses, etc. And CLVII does that too. The out-of-the-way, sorta hushed-tone-feel of the place is embodied in CLVII Beirut too. The showroom looks kinda tiny, but, when you start getting interested and want more, the large mirror in the middle is actually a “hidden” door which is opened up and lets you into the much larger back rooms.</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://ginoraidy.files.wordpress.com/2013/02/032912-music-jason-derulo-broken-neck1.jpg\"><img alt=\"032912-music-jason-derulo-broken-neck\" src=\"http://ginoraidy.files.wordpress.com/2013/02/032912-music-jason-derulo-broken-neck1.jpg?w=300&h=168\" width=\"300\" height=\"168\"></a>That’s where a wider selection of items, pieces of art and fitting happens. Now, price-wise, it could be up to 2000K to customize a women’s blazer with 24-karat gold studs. But, it could be a good-old Yankees cup with studs for much, much less. Personally, the thing that got me was that you could bring in your own stuff, and get them to customize it for you, and I do mean everything. Julien even studded Jason De Rulo’s neck brace with black diamonds…</p>\n<p>So, if you’re into the more funky, urban type of fashion, a fan of Kanye (yuck), Lil Wayne (meh), Rihanna (Yes please) or Wiz (HELL YES!) then you might enjoy this store. The guys and gals that run it are really nice and helpful, but not incessant in their flattery like “wow, yes, this looks great on you” just to make a sale. They’ll just say “no, that’s not it” or “this is way too expensive” if it doesn’t fit the budget you set for yourself and I loved that honesty in an often “7arboo2″ type of salesmanship in Beirut.</p>\n<p>It’s located in Saifi Village and here’s their <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/clviibeirut?ref=ts&fref=ts\">Facebook page</a>.</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://ginoraidy.files.wordpress.com/2013/02/wpid-20130226_124557.jpg\">\n</a><a href=\"http://ginosblog.com/2013/02/27/clvii-customized-and-unique-fashion-opens-in-first-branch-outside-of-paris-in-beirut/wpid-20130226_124157-jpg/\" title=\"wpid-20130226_124157.jpg\"><img width=\"112\" height=\"150\" src=\"http://ginoraidy.files.wordpress.com/2013/02/wpid-20130226_124157.jpg?w=112&h=150\" alt=\"wpid-20130226_124157.jpg\"></a>\n<a href=\"http://ginosblog.com/2013/02/27/clvii-customized-and-unique-fashion-opens-in-first-branch-outside-of-paris-in-beirut/wpid-20130226_124314-jpg/\" title=\"wpid-20130226_124314.jpg\"><img width=\"112\" height=\"150\" src=\"http://ginoraidy.files.wordpress.com/2013/02/wpid-20130226_124314.jpg?w=112&h=150\" alt=\"wpid-20130226_124314.jpg\"></a>\n<a href=\"http://ginosblog.com/2013/02/27/clvii-customized-and-unique-fashion-opens-in-first-branch-outside-of-paris-in-beirut/wpid-20130226_124047-jpg/\" title=\"wpid-20130226_124047.jpg\"><img width=\"112\" height=\"150\" src=\"http://ginoraidy.files.wordpress.com/2013/02/wpid-20130226_124047.jpg?w=112&h=150\" alt=\"wpid-20130226_124047.jpg\"></a>\n<a href=\"http://ginosblog.com/2013/02/27/clvii-customized-and-unique-fashion-opens-in-first-branch-outside-of-paris-in-beirut/wpid-20130226_124610-jpg/\" title=\"wpid-20130226_124610.jpg\"><img width=\"112\" height=\"150\" src=\"http://ginoraidy.files.wordpress.com/2013/02/wpid-20130226_124610.jpg?w=112&h=150\" alt=\"wpid-20130226_124610.jpg\"></a>\n<a href=\"http://ginosblog.com/2013/02/27/clvii-customized-and-unique-fashion-opens-in-first-branch-outside-of-paris-in-beirut/wpid-20130226_124645-jpg/\" title=\"wpid-20130226_124645.jpg\"><img width=\"112\" height=\"150\" src=\"http://ginoraidy.files.wordpress.com/2013/02/wpid-20130226_124645.jpg?w=112&h=150\" alt=\"wpid-20130226_124645.jpg\"></a>\n<a href=\"http://ginosblog.com/2013/02/27/clvii-customized-and-unique-fashion-opens-in-first-branch-outside-of-paris-in-beirut/wpid-20130226_124146-jpg/\" title=\"wpid-20130226_124146.jpg\"><img width=\"112\" height=\"150\" src=\"http://ginoraidy.files.wordpress.com/2013/02/wpid-20130226_124146.jpg?w=112&h=150\" alt=\"wpid-20130226_124146.jpg\"></a>\n<a href=\"http://ginosblog.com/2013/02/27/clvii-customized-and-unique-fashion-opens-in-first-branch-outside-of-paris-in-beirut/wpid-20130226_124035-jpg/\" title=\"wpid-20130226_124035.jpg\"><img width=\"150\" height=\"112\" src=\"http://ginoraidy.files.wordpress.com/2013/02/wpid-20130226_124035.jpg?w=150&h=112\" alt=\"wpid-20130226_124035.jpg\"></a>\n<a href=\"http://ginosblog.com/2013/02/27/clvii-customized-and-unique-fashion-opens-in-first-branch-outside-of-paris-in-beirut/wpid-20130226_124444-jpg/\" title=\"wpid-20130226_124444.jpg\"><img width=\"112\" height=\"150\" src=\"http://ginoraidy.files.wordpress.com/2013/02/wpid-20130226_124444.jpg?w=112&h=150\" alt=\"wpid-20130226_124444.jpg\"></a>\n<a href=\"http://ginosblog.com/2013/02/27/clvii-customized-and-unique-fashion-opens-in-first-branch-outside-of-paris-in-beirut/wpid-20130226_124512-jpg/\" title=\"wpid-20130226_124512.jpg\"><img width=\"112\" height=\"150\" src=\"http://ginoraidy.files.wordpress.com/2013/02/wpid-20130226_124512.jpg?w=112&h=150\" alt=\"wpid-20130226_124512.jpg\"></a>\n<a href=\"http://ginosblog.com/2013/02/27/clvii-customized-and-unique-fashion-opens-in-first-branch-outside-of-paris-in-beirut/wpid-20130226_124302-jpg/\" title=\"wpid-20130226_124302.jpg\"><img width=\"112\" height=\"150\" src=\"http://ginoraidy.files.wordpress.com/2013/02/wpid-20130226_124302.jpg?w=112&h=150\" alt=\"wpid-20130226_124302.jpg\"></a>\n<a href=\"http://ginosblog.com/2013/02/27/clvii-customized-and-unique-fashion-opens-in-first-branch-outside-of-paris-in-beirut/wpid-20130226_124016-jpg/\" title=\"wpid-20130226_124016.jpg\"><img width=\"150\" height=\"112\" src=\"http://ginoraidy.files.wordpress.com/2013/02/wpid-20130226_124016.jpg?w=150&h=112\" alt=\"wpid-20130226_124016.jpg\"></a>\n<a href=\"http://ginosblog.com/2013/02/27/clvii-customized-and-unique-fashion-opens-in-first-branch-outside-of-paris-in-beirut/wpid-20130226_124231-jpg/\" title=\"wpid-20130226_124231.jpg\"><img width=\"112\" height=\"150\" src=\"http://ginoraidy.files.wordpress.com/2013/02/wpid-20130226_124231.jpg?w=112&h=150\" alt=\"wpid-20130226_124231.jpg\"></a>\n<a href=\"http://ginosblog.com/2013/02/27/clvii-customized-and-unique-fashion-opens-in-first-branch-outside-of-paris-in-beirut/wpid-20130226_124427-jpg/\" title=\"wpid-20130226_124427.jpg\"><img width=\"112\" height=\"150\" src=\"http://ginoraidy.files.wordpress.com/2013/02/wpid-20130226_124427.jpg?w=112&h=150\" alt=\"wpid-20130226_124427.jpg\"></a>\n<a href=\"http://ginosblog.com/2013/02/27/clvii-customized-and-unique-fashion-opens-in-first-branch-outside-of-paris-in-beirut/wpid-20130226_124221-jpg/\" title=\"wpid-20130226_124221.jpg\"><img width=\"112\" height=\"150\" src=\"http://ginoraidy.files.wordpress.com/2013/02/wpid-20130226_124221.jpg?w=112&h=150\" alt=\"wpid-20130226_124221.jpg\"></a>\n<a href=\"http://ginosblog.com/2013/02/27/clvii-customized-and-unique-fashion-opens-in-first-branch-outside-of-paris-in-beirut/wpid-20130226_124605-jpg/\" title=\"wpid-20130226_124605.jpg\"><img width=\"150\" height=\"112\" src=\"http://ginoraidy.files.wordpress.com/2013/02/wpid-20130226_124605.jpg?w=150&h=112\" alt=\"wpid-20130226_124605.jpg\"></a>\n<a href=\"http://ginosblog.com/2013/02/27/clvii-customized-and-unique-fashion-opens-in-first-branch-outside-of-paris-in-beirut/wpid-20130226_124135-jpg/\" title=\"wpid-20130226_124135.jpg\"><img width=\"112\" height=\"150\" src=\"http://ginoraidy.files.wordpress.com/2013/02/wpid-20130226_124135.jpg?w=112&h=150\" alt=\"wpid-20130226_124135.jpg\"></a>\n<a href=\"http://ginosblog.com/2013/02/27/clvii-customized-and-unique-fashion-opens-in-first-branch-outside-of-paris-in-beirut/wpid-20130226_124334-jpg/\" title=\"wpid-20130226_124334.jpg\"><img width=\"112\" height=\"150\" src=\"http://ginoraidy.files.wordpress.com/2013/02/wpid-20130226_124334.jpg?w=112&h=150\" alt=\"wpid-20130226_124334.jpg\"></a>\n<a href=\"http://ginosblog.com/2013/02/27/clvii-customized-and-unique-fashion-opens-in-first-branch-outside-of-paris-in-beirut/wpid-20130226_124202-jpg/\" title=\"wpid-20130226_124202.jpg\"><img width=\"112\" height=\"150\" src=\"http://ginoraidy.files.wordpress.com/2013/02/wpid-20130226_124202.jpg?w=112&h=150\" alt=\"wpid-20130226_124202.jpg\"></a>\n<a href=\"http://ginosblog.com/2013/02/27/clvii-customized-and-unique-fashion-opens-in-first-branch-outside-of-paris-in-beirut/wpid-20130226_124106-jpg/\" title=\"wpid-20130226_124106.jpg\"><img width=\"112\" height=\"150\" src=\"http://ginoraidy.files.wordpress.com/2013/02/wpid-20130226_124106.jpg?w=112&h=150\" alt=\"wpid-20130226_124106.jpg\"></a>\n<a href=\"http://ginosblog.com/2013/02/27/clvii-customized-and-unique-fashion-opens-in-first-branch-outside-of-paris-in-beirut/wpid-20130226_124122-jpg/\" title=\"wpid-20130226_124122.jpg\"><img width=\"112\" height=\"150\" src=\"http://ginoraidy.files.wordpress.com/2013/02/wpid-20130226_124122.jpg?w=112&h=150\" alt=\"wpid-20130226_124122.jpg\"></a>\n<a href=\"http://ginosblog.com/2013/02/27/clvii-customized-and-unique-fashion-opens-in-first-branch-outside-of-paris-in-beirut/wpid-20130226_124557-jpg/\" title=\"wpid-20130226_124557.jpg\"><img width=\"112\" height=\"150\" src=\"http://ginoraidy.files.wordpress.com/2013/02/wpid-20130226_124557.jpg?w=112&h=150\" alt=\"wpid-20130226_124557.jpg\"></a>\n<br></p>\n<div></div>\n<br><a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/gocomments/ginoraidy.wordpress.com/12273/\"><img alt=\"\" border=\"0\" src=\"http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/comments/ginoraidy.wordpress.com/12273/\"></a> <img alt=\"\" border=\"0\" src=\"http://stats.wordpress.com/b.gif?host=ginosblog.com&blog=11198665&post=12273&subd=ginoraidy&ref=&feed=1\" width=\"1\" height=\"1\">'),
	(95,'http://blogbaladi.com/fun-facts-about-sheikh-ahmad-al-assir/','Fun Facts about Sheikh Ahmad Al-Assir','http://blogbaladi.com/images/2013-02-08t131210z_1995018188_gm1e9281mn801_rtrmadp_3_lebanon-clashes-425x290.jpg','Source\nHe’s an Android fan (Samsung S2 maybe?) and he drinks what looks like a Contrex or a Nestle Pure Life Pink Bott...','blogbaladi',1361958540,'<p><img src=\"http://blogbaladi.com/images/2013-02-08t131210z_1995018188_gm1e9281mn801_rtrmadp_3_lebanon-clashes-425x290.jpg\" alt=\"Sunni Muslim Salafist leader Ahmad al-Assir addresses his supporters during a protest in Beirut\" width=\"425\" height=\"290\"><br><em><a href=\"http://msnbcmedia.msn.com/i/reuters/2013-02-08t131210z_1995018188_gm1e9281mn801_rtrmadp_3_lebanon-clashes.jpg\">Source</a><br></em></p>\n<p>He’s an Android fan (Samsung S2 maybe?) and he drinks what looks like a Contrex or a Nestle Pure Life Pink Bottle. </p>\n<p>This post reminded me for some reason of Mark’s <a href=\"http://248am.com/mark/kuwait/the-ultimate-water-review/\">Ultimate Water review</a>.</p>\n<p><img src=\"http://blogbaladi.com/images/assir-425x230.jpg\" alt=\"assir\" width=\"425\" height=\"230\"></p>'),
